1.title: Poikaystävä (Boyfriend)
1.plot: Brenda seduces Jukka, the boyfriend of her twin sister Kelly, and makes sure, that Kelly catches them in the act.

2.title: Pääsiäiserikois (Easter Special)
2.plot: Brenda has a special Easter surprise for her twin sister Kelly.

3.title: Sukupuolitauti (STD)
3.plot: Kelly finds out that she has an STD. She knows that she has gotten it from her boyfriend Jukka who must have gotten it from her evil twin sister Brenda. Kelly confronts Brenda, while Jukka is too embarssed to talk about it.

4.title: Häät (Wedding)
4.plot: Brenda ruins the wedding of her twin sister Kelly.

5.title: Syntärri (Happy Birthday)
5.plot: To have a little fun on her birthday, Brenda ruins the birthday party of her twin sister Kelly by telling all her friends that Kelly is dead.

6.title: Musti (Blacky)
6.plot: Kelly's beloved dog Blacky is gone and Brenda just got a new black fur jacket. Coincidence?

7.title: Äitienpäivä-Erikois (Mother's Day Special)
7.plot: Kelly finds out that she is pregnant, but has no idea how it happened. Only her evil twin sister Brenda knows the truth.

imdb.plot outline: SISKOT (SISTERS) is a soap opera parody about the twin sisters Kelly and Brenda. Both sisters are exaggerated soap opera characters. While Kelly has a heart of gold, Brenda is completely evil. These simple outlines are the main driving force for the characters and the story. According to this, in each episode, Brenda finds new ways to torture Kelly. Sleeping with her boyfriend, spoiling her birthday party and ruining her wedding, is just the beginning. The show aims at reaching an international audiences and therefore, is multi-lingual: each episode of SISKOT is produced and broadcast in Finnish, English, and German.
